      "date": "2023-09-23 22:39:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nHappy to see the perl being removed here.\n\nI just noticed that sanity.sh::test_103 is calling tests/acl/run, which is also implemented in perl and will likely be less easy to replace.\n\nIn the meantime, it should also get a check if perl is installed, something like:\n\n         LANG=C perl -MPOSIX -e ';' || skip_env \"no POSIX perl module installed\"\n\nso that it is skipped if not installed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
